$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'In mathematica et computatrum scientia, hexadecimalis (etiam basi 16, vel hex) est systema numeralis positivus cum radix vel basis, 16. Utitur symbolis sedecim distinctis, saepissime symbolis 0-9, ut valores nulla ad novem repraesentent; et A, B, C, D, E, F (vel a-f) valores decem ad quindecim repraesentantes. Exempli gratia, numerus hexadecimalis 2AF3 est aequalis in decimali, ut (2 163) + (10 162) + (15 161) + (3 160) vel 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Quisque digitus hexadecimalis quattuor binarios digitos (bitulas) (etiam &quot;nibble&quot; nominat, et primus usus notationis hexadecimalis est sicut humanus-amicus repraesentatio valorum binariorum coded in computandis et electronicis digitalibus. Exempli gratia, valores byte ab 0 usque ad 255 vagari possunt, sed commodius ut duo digiti hexadecimales in latitudine 00 per FF commodius exprimantur. Hexadecimal etiam communiter ad inscriptiones computatrum memorias repraesentandas adhibetur.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex abbreviatio hexadecimali est, quae funda -16 structura innititur et ad simpliciorem modum adhibetur quomodo instructiones ad computatores repraesententur. Haec XVI symbolorum numerorum ratio evoluta est ut instrumentum numeri inhibendi 8 bis binarii, ut notitia sine labore in computatoribus encoded possit. Potest imprimi et figurari utens duobus digitis hexametris diversi cum singulis digiti hexametris nibble vel fortasse 4-partilis formando demonstrans.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Hic numerus systematis utitur 16 symbolis quae in range ex 0-9 vel AF repraesentantur. 0-9 repraesentant numeri usque ad novem, AF vero per numerum 10-15 repraesentatur. Ad reliqua tria genera systematum numerorum comparati, ratio numeralis hexadecimalis efficacissima esse censetur.';
